### Request for Proposal: Baker Lake Perimeter Fence System {#r4p-clôture-de-périmètre-de-baker-lake}
### {#r4p-clôture-de-périmètre-de-baker-lake}

#### Project Overview {#proj-overview}
The Department of Public Works and Government Services (PSPC) is soliciting proposals for a perimeter fence system to serve Natural Resources Canada's facility at Baker Lake, Nunavut. The fence system must meet the requirements outlined in the Statement of Requirement in the Request for Proposal.

#### Proposal Requirements {#pr-requirements}
- Proposals must be conditionally limited to Canadian goods.
- Deliveries will be made duty-paid (DDP) to Ottawa, Ontario, for furtherance to Baker Lake, Nunavut.
- The perimeter fence system must comply with the requirements outlined in the Statement of Requirement.

#### Debriefing or Feedback Session {#db-feedback}
A debriefing or feedback session will be provided upon request to bidders who bid on the previous solicitation (14953504) dated December 22, 2022.

#### Important Notes {#imp-notes}
- This procurement is conditionally limited to Canadian goods.
- Items to be delivered to Baker Lake, Nunavut, are subject to the Nunavut Land Claim Agreement (NLCA).

#### Request for Proposal Information {#r4pinformation}
